	REF: PWM control of 4A, 12 VDC motors with an LMD18200-based
	      H-bridge
	     HandyBoard


	Greetings,

	Two LMD18200s apparently can be 'bridged', being then capable
	of currents of 6A (average) and 12 A (peak). This information
	is based on specifications reported by Wirz Electronics on the
	page
		http://wirz.com/motor/board.html

	I have acquired a non-bridged kit from that company and will
	report results as soon as I test it, if you so desire.

	Thank you for your attention.

